      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we want something along these lines here:\n\n  // Validate the available reader size *before* attempting to allocate, to prevent OOM attacks.\n  const auto glyphsSize \u003d glyphCount * sizeof(uint16_t),\n                posSize \u003d glyphCount * sizeof(SkScalar) * ScalarsPerGlyph(pos),\n            clusterSize \u003d pe.extended ? glyphCount * sizeof(uint32_t) : 0,\n              totalSize \u003d glyphsSize + posSize + clusterSize + textSize;\n\n  if (!reader.isValid() || reader.size() \u003c totalSize) {\n      return nullptr;\n  }\n\nUsing SkSafeMath would not hurt either.\n\nAnyway, I can do this in a follow-up - let\u0027s land your current fix for now to close that issue.",
